    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>African stone palaces. The outer walls and cattle kraals were built of dressed stone while the main buildings within the walls were of mud and wattle construction.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011331/Denyer, African Traditional Architecture (1978)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Palacio de piedra africano. Las paredes exteriores y los corrales del ganado fueron construidas de piedra revestida mientras que los edificios principales dentro de las murallas fueron construido con lodo y agua</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afrikaanse stenen paleizen. De buitenste muren en veekralen werden gebouwd van bedekte stenen, terwijl de hoofdgebouwen binnen de muren werden gemaakt van constructies van leem en vlechtwerk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>非洲石砌宮殿，其外牆及牲畜欄舍由磨光之石塊砌成，牆內的主建築則以泥漿及枝條建造。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
